main event: An explosion was reported by an aircraft at 25,000 feet over the Pacific Ocean on November 9, 1962.
interesting points: The explosion was described as a mid-air detonation with a long-lasting cloud of smoke., The incident was recorded with ground-radar and weak-visual observations., Conclusions from the report suggested it was likely a missile explosion., The coordinates of the incident were 35-00N 127-00W., The report was part of Project 10073 and contains multiple incoming messages.
witness description: Reported by an aircraft flying at 25,000 feet.
